nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Glycine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network targets glycine through a connected prebiotic graph spanning hydrothermal carbon fixation, surface cyanosulfidic/Strecker chemistry, and biochemical hydrolysis/amination steps. The design follows literature-supported routes centered on formaldehyde, hydrogen cyanide, glyconitrile, aminoacetonitrile, glycolic acid, and glyoxylate as major intermediates. Convergence occurs at formaldehyde, aminoacetonitrile, glyoxylate, and glycine. Ten distinct pathways are represented as different valid route combinations through shared reactions and hubs, linking hydrothermal production of C1/C2 feedstocks to surface nitrile chemistry and final aqueous conversion to glycine.\n\nMOLECULES (15 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_006: CH3NO (aminomethanol) [intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C2H3NO (glycolonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C2H4N2 (aminoacetonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C2H4O3 (glycolic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C2H2O3 (glyoxylic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: H2S (hydrogen sulfide) [starting]\n  - mol_012: C3H4O3 (pyruvic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C2H5NO2 (glycine) [target]\n  - mol_014: CHNO (formamide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_015: H2O (water) [starting]\n\nREACTIONS (12 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_003 (Hydrothermal CO2 reduction to formaldehyde-equivalent C1 feedstock) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_003, mol_015 -> mol_009 (Hydrothermal formaldehyde oxidation to glycolic acid) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_012 (Hydrothermal synthesis of pyruvate from reduced carbon and CO2