quences or glycolaldehyde/glycolic acid intermediacy.\",\n        \"Specify a plausible anoxic oxidation mechanism for rxn_011, such as UV/TiO2-mediated photoredox or mineral redox cycling.\",\n        \"For rxn_015, distinguish between direct reductive amination and transamination and include reductant or amino donor.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P5\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_002\": 0.45,\n        \"rxn_004\": 0.3,\n        \"rxn_006\": 0.92,\n        \"rxn_010\": 0.68,\n        \"rxn_015\": 0.52\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.57,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.72,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.82,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.7,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.67,\n      \"feedback\": \"This pathway captures the literature idea that cyanosulfidic chemistry can connect glyconitrile/glycolonitrile to glyoxylate-related products and ultimately glycine. However, the network compresses a multistep, spatially separated cyanosulfidic sequence into a single conversion. The final glyoxylate-to-glycine step is also underspecified. Good conceptual relevance, limited mechanistic detail.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_002\",\n        \"rxn_004\",\n        \"rxn_010\",\n        \"rxn_015\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Expand rxn_010 into multiple literature-consistent photoredox and hydrolysis steps rather than a one-node shortcut.\",\n        \"Acknowledge the need for spatiotemporal separation explicitly in the pathway definition.\",\n        \"Specify UV dependence and sulfide-mediated redox chemistry more clearly.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P6\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_001\": 0.9,\n        \"rxn_002\": 0.45,\n        \"rxn_004\": 0.3,\n        \"rxn_006\": 0.92,\n        \"rxn_007\": 0.72,\n        \"rxn_012\": 0.86\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.67,\n      \"pathway_coherenc